# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this React + Vite project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` version 2.0.0 using npm
- Package added to dependencies in `package.json`

### 2. Component Integration
- Modified `client/src/App.jsx` to import and include the SpeedInsights component
- Added `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/react";`
- Wrapped the AppRoutes component in a React Fragment to include SpeedInsights
- Placed SpeedInsights component at the root level to track all pages

### 3. Files Modified
- `client/package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- `client/package-lock.json` - Updated with new package and dependencies
- `client/src/App.jsx` - Added SpeedInsights component

## Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel Speed Insights documentation (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart) for React applications:

1. **Framework Identified**: React 19.2.7 with Vite 8.1.1
2. **Package Manager**: npm (detected from package-lock.json)
3. **Integration Point**: App.jsx (root component)

The SpeedInsights component is placed at the root level of the application alongside the AppRoutes component, ensuring it can properly track performance metrics across all pages and routes.

## Verification Steps Completed

✅ Package installed successfully (npm install @vercel/speed-insights)
✅ Build verification passed (npm run build)
✅ Linter check passed (npm run lint - no new errors introduced)
✅ No tests configured in project (skipped test verification)
✅ Lock files updated (package-lock.json)

## Next Steps

To start collecting Speed Insights data:
1. Enable Speed Insights in your Vercel project dashboard
2. Deploy the application to Vercel
3. Wait for user traffic to accumulate
4. View metrics in the Vercel dashboard after a few days

The Speed Insights component is now active and will automatically begin collecting performance metrics when deployed to Vercel.
